<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=7390&amp;p=86726#p86726"><![CDATA[
In my music engine, all drums go through the sound effects engine. The kick drum in the opening to <a href="http://nesdev.com/bbs/viewtopic.php?p=84524#84524" class="postlink">Zap Ruder</a>, for example, is one sound effect played on the triangle channel and another sound effect on the noise channel. This way the drum sound naturally interrupts whatever's behind it.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=9">tepples</a> — Wed Nov 23, 2011 5:10 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
